snippet.textDisplay: I want to hear the album with better word play by any rapper ever on any album than kamikaze..? Or why walk on water isn’t lyrically great? I don’t love this album although I appreciate him trying to make each one sound different instead of selling me the same album different words, something only rappers like him and Kendrick, very few I’ll just say actually do..  this one while not my favorite, it’s better than most, but the previous two , seriously I’d love a non fake be brutally honest with urself discussion explaining the album u think has better word play than kamikazee, if your not bias, or just plain not smart, than let’s here the album and help me discover a better one.  Cause just his cadence and sound makes him far from my favorite, but that’s a preference thing and since he’s the most popular rapper ever, him and drake, so clearly plenty do... but pretending there are that many rap songs lyrically better than Dark or yes WALK ON WATER, it’s just like watching some idiot tell people Brady throwing for five touchdowns in a game is trash cause they hate they way he looks doing it to me..  facts is u can’t list to many songs better lyrically than dark, or WW, or the that u know of no album with better word play than Kamikaze cause to my knowledge there’s never been one, but it’s trash cause he sounds bitter to u..  the layers in a song like not a like and the relevancy of them, never compromising the message or rhyme scheme and can’t find a word that seemingly he could have used a more relevant one in place of, but still multiple layers to it, I just don’t know of a better album that way and been a rap feen for longer than u been alive,.  I don’t think I’m dumb, I teach surgeons for a living and help during surgery’s with the equipment my company owns and have for almost two decades, that or highly specialized unique delivery and complex pharmacokinetic drugs I’ve rep’d, and don’t at all mean to say I’m anything more than anyone else, just I think I’ve proven to not be dumb, yet want to know the albums I’m missing better layered than Kamikaze was.. also, why for example ww, I want to hear maybe a J Cole song that’s better lyrically, cause I for one only know of Kendrick I’ve heard with the pen Em has sometimes, well maybe Black thought, My fav at least, seen more than any other musician, I’m not sure you’ll find many verses better than Em’s on WW on many Roots albums though if I’m honest and hate saying that!  Even track two on revival, tell me five albums why it’s trash when my common sense is telling me it’s great..?  rhymes the entire sentences and is as layered and to my ear with the exception of the fanny packs hour glass bar they’re hard to me.. to be honest I’ve heard myself say more than anyone else that “I wish he’d concern himself with a bar being corny more than layered more often” including this album where even with far more punchlines and layers than kamikazee, but has its share of corny bars and forced bars like document shredder for example, the reason it don’t touch his last one word play wise for me,songs like not alike, most actually, he doesn’t ever compromise the ryme or message, and every word is so relevant in his layers even without them u won’t find one where a different word clearly works better, I just want to know the album better word play wise than Kamikazee, and if there ain’t ever been one , how the best one ever in such a staple way of being a great lyricist, how can’t it be great let alone not good?  Even if u don’t like his sound, u can’t argue most do, so why.  And I’d love to hear why songs like Kim on revival it’s the same ryme scheme he won an Oscar for but class A story telling rap and more complex as well, why that or the first two, castle and arose, why are they not lyrically great and show me the, I don’t know, j Cole we’ll say, show me his album with just that number of songs better lyrically than those are, especially the most hated on WW one

snippet.textDisplay:
I think there is a solid 8.5 - 9.0 out of 10 album here, but it was overcrowded, and needed some trimming. They always could have made a bonus version of the album and added the other cuts back in that version.

1) Premonition (2:53)
2) You Gon Learn (3:36)
3) Lock it Up (2:50)
4) Godzilla (3:30)
5) Alfred (interlude) (0:30)
6) Darkness (5:37)
7) Leaving Heaven (4:25)
8) Marsh (3:20)
9) Little Engine (2:57)
10) Yah Yah (4:47)
11) No Regrets (3:20)
12) I Will (5:03)
13) Alfred (outro) (0:39)
Total 43:27

It would have been in-between Illmatic and Reasonable Doubt length. Nice and to the point. I feel like rappers tend to add too many filler tracks to boost length. Even on my favorite old-school albums, there's a lot of filler.

snippet.textDisplay: Actually, Marsh is one of my favorites, the chorus is super catchy and most of those "corny lines" you mentioned in Marsh and others don't really seem that corny at all, to me at least. Also, my favorite chorus are probably from I Will, Marsh and Unaccomodating just because I find them so catchy and can't get them out of my head, which is kinda funny because those are the one you stood out as bad. Well, I guess taste really is subjective! He's rarely direct in his verses so having more basic yet cool lines is typical of him and don't really think it instantly means they are "corny", he's also always had those "corny" lines throughout his career for humor or style purposes and I think that's what happens here too, hence me not thinking they're "corny". I think most of them at least are on purpose for stylistic reasons like we've always seen from him. But ya know, just wanted to leave that thought here and my personal experience with the album! Have a good day.
